2️⃣ Workload Objects (VERY Important for Interviews)

🔴 Pod Lifecycle -------------------------------
  🔹 Phases: Pending → Running → Succeeded/Failed → Terminated
  🔹 Key idea: Pod is created → scheduled → runs containers → exits or restarts
  🔹 Important: Restart handled by controller (Deployment/Job), not Pod itself
  🔹 Interview tip: Pod is ephemeral → never rely on it for persistent state

🔴 Deployments ---------------------------------
  🔹 Definition: High-level controller to manage stateless applications
  🔹 Key idea: Manages ReplicaSets → Pods + supports rolling updates & rollbacks
  🔹 Important: Handles scaling, self-healing, versioning automatically
  🔹 Interview tip: Use Deployment for most apps (stateless), not for stateful workloads

🔴 ReplicaSet -----------------------------------
  🔹 Definition: Ensures a specified number of pod replicas are always running
  🔹 Key idea: If a pod fails → ReplicaSet recreates it automatically
  🔹 Important: Usually managed by Deployment (not used directly)
  🔹 Interview tip: Deployment = higher-level controller, ReplicaSet = actual pod manager

🔴 StatefulSets (when & why) ------------------
  🔹 Definition: Manages stateful applications with stable identity (name, storage, network)
  🔹 When to use: Databases, queues (e.g., ordered pods + persistent storage required)
  🔹 Key idea: Pods are created in order (0 → n) with stable names + persistent volumes
  🔹 Interview tip: Use StatefulSet when you need stable identity + storage (unlike Deployment)

🔴 DaemonSet ------------------------------
  🔹 Definition: Ensures one pod runs on every node (or selected nodes)
  🔹 Key idea: Auto-add/remove pods when nodes join/leave cluster
  🔹 Use cases: Monitoring (Prometheus Node Exporter), logging (Fluentd), networking agents
  🔹 Interview tip: Use DaemonSet for node-level services (not app workloads)

🔴 Jobs And CronJobs --------------------------------
  🔹 Job: Runs one-time task until completion (e.g., migration, batch job)
  🔹 CronJob: Runs Jobs on a schedule (cron format)
  🔹 Key idea: Job = run once | CronJob = run repeatedly
  🔹 Interview tip: Use CronJob for backups/cleanup, Job for one-time tasks
   

🔴 Rolling updates & rollbacks --------------------
  🔹 Rolling Update: Gradually replaces old pods with new ones → zero downtime deployment
  🔹 Key config: maxUnavailable (pods down) & maxSurge (extra pods during update)
  🔹 Rollback: Reverts to previous ReplicaSet/version if deployment fails
  🔹 Interview tip: Use readiness probes + rollout undo for safe deployments
