3️⃣ Kubernetes Networking (High-frequency interview area)

🔴 Services (ClusterIP, NodePort, LoadBalancer) -------------------------------
  🔹 ClusterIP: Default → internal access only (pod ↔ pod communication)
  🔹 NodePort: Exposes service on Node IP + static port (30000–32767)
  🔹 LoadBalancer: Creates external load balancer (cloud) for public access
  🔹 Interview tip: Use ClusterIP internally, LoadBalancer/Ingress for external traffic
          
🔴 DNS -------------------------------
  🔹 Definition: Provides service discovery using names instead of IPs
  🔹 Core component: CoreDNS resolves service → ClusterIP
  🔹 Format: <service>.<namespace>.svc.cluster.local (FQDN)
  🔹 Interview tip: DNS failure → check CoreDNS + Service + Endpoints

🔴 Ingress vs Ingress Controller ---------------------------------
  🔹 Ingress: YAML resource defining routing rules (host/path → service)
  🔹 Ingress Controller: Actual component (e.g., NGINX Ingress Controller) that implements those rules
  🔹 Key idea: Ingress = what to do | Controller = does the work
  🔹 Interview tip: Ingress alone does nothing → controller must be installed

🔴 Network Policies --------------------------
  🔹 Definition: Pod-level firewall to control ingress & egress traffic
  🔹 Key idea: Default = allow all → once policy applied = deny all except allowed
  🔹 Important: Works only with CNI like Calico / Cilium
  🔹 Interview tip: Start with deny-all + allow required traffic only
