7️⃣ Kubernetes Security (Hot Interview Topic 🔥)

🔴 RBAC (Roles, ClusterRoles, Bindings) ----------------
  🔹 Role: Defines permissions within a namespace (e.g., read pods in dev)
  🔹 ClusterRole: Defines permissions cluster-wide (or reusable across namespaces)
  🔹 Bindings:
    RoleBinding: Attach Role to user/service account in a namespace
    ClusterRoleBinding: Attach ClusterRole at cluster level
  🔹 Interview tip: Role = namespace scope, ClusterRole = cluster scope, Binding = who gets access

🔴 Service Accounts ------------------
  🔹 Definition: Identity used by pods to interact with Kubernetes API
  🔹 Key idea: Pods use ServiceAccount + token to authenticate (via RBAC)
  🔹 Important: Default SA exists in every namespace → should avoid using default in production
  🔹 Interview tip: Always create dedicated ServiceAccount + least privilege RBAC

🔴 Pod Security Standards (PSS) -----------------
  🔹 Definition: Built-in security standards to control pod security levels (replaces PodSecurityPolicies)
  🔹 Levels:
    Privileged (least secure, full access)
    Baseline (basic restrictions)
    Restricted (most secure, production recommended)
  🔹 Key idea: Enforced via namespace labels (e.g., pod-security.kubernetes.io/enforce=restricted)
  🔹 Interview tip: Always aim for Restricted policy in production for strong security

🔴 Image security & scanning ----------------
  🔹 Definition: Process of ensuring container images are free from vulnerabilities & misconfigurations
  🔹 Key idea: Scan images before deploy using tools like Trivy / Clair
  🔹 Best practices: Use minimal base images (Alpine/distroless) + avoid latest tag + regularly update images
  🔹 Interview tip: Shift-left security → scan in CI/CD before pushing to registry

🔴 Secrets encryption ----------------
  🔹 Definition: Encrypts Kubernetes Secrets at rest in etcd to prevent plain-text storage
  🔹 Key idea: By default secrets are only Base64 encoded (not secure) → enable encryptionConfiguration
  🔹 Methods: aescbc (recommended), kms (cloud KMS integration), secretbox
  🔹 Interview tip: Always enable etcd encryption + KMS for production-grade security
