🔴 Storage Class ==================================================
  a StorageClass defines how storage should be dynamically provisioned.
  🎯 Why StorageClass Is Needed
    Without StorageClass:
      Admin must manually create PVs
      Developers depend on infra team
      Scaling becomes difficult
    
    With StorageClass:
      PVC triggers automatic volume creation
      No manual PV creation needed
      Works seamlessly in cloud environments

  🏗️ Storage Architecture Flow
    Pod → PVC → StorageClass → Provisioner → PV → Cloud Disk

  Flow Explained:
    Developer creates PVC
    PVC references a StorageClass
    Kubernetes calls provisioner
    PV is dynamically created
    Pod mounts the PVC

  🆚 StorageClass vs PersistentVolume
  Feature	 -               StorageClass	                        PersistentVolume
  Purpose	 -               Defines how storage is created	      Represents actual storage
  Dynamic provisioning -	 Yes	                                No
  Cloud integration	  -    Yes	                                Manual
