1️⃣2️⃣ Troubleshooting & Debugging (Interview Killer Skill)

🔴 Pod crash loops --------------
  🔹 Symptom: Pod keeps restarting → status = CrashLoopBackOff
  🔹 Possible causes: App crash, wrong config/env, missing dependency (DB/API), port conflict
  🔹 Debug steps:
    kubectl logs <pod> (check error)
    kubectl describe pod <pod> (events, exit code)
    kubectl get pods -o wide (node info)
  🔹 Interview tip: Always check logs first → then events → then config

🔴 Image pull issues ------------------
  🔹 Symptom: Pod stuck in ImagePullBackOff / ErrImagePull
  🔹 Possible causes: Wrong image name/tag, private repo auth issue, network/DNS issue
  🔹 Debug steps:
    kubectl describe pod <pod> (check pull error)
    Verify image name/tag
    Check imagePullSecrets / registry access
  🔹 Interview tip: 90% cases = wrong image tag or missing credentials

🔴 DNS failures -----------------
  🔹 Symptom: Service not reachable via name (e.g., backend-service not resolving)
  🔹 Possible causes: CoreDNS down, wrong service name/namespace, network/CNI issue
  🔹 Debug steps:
    kubectl exec -it <pod> -- nslookup <service>
    kubectl get pods -n kube-system (check CoreDNS)
    kubectl get svc,ep (verify service & endpoints)
  🔹 Interview tip: Always check DNS → Service → Endpoints → Network in order

🔴 Network issues ------------------
  🔹 Symptom: Pods can’t communicate (timeout / connection refused)
  🔹 Possible causes: CNI issue (Calico / Cilium), wrong Service/labels, NetworkPolicy blocking
  🔹 Debug steps:
    kubectl get pods -o wide (IP check)
    kubectl get svc,ep (endpoints exist?)
    kubectl exec -it <pod> -- curl <service>
    Check NetworkPolicies
  🔹 Interview tip: Always verify Pod → Service → Endpoints → NetworkPolicy → CNI

